.TH DRQ 1 "March 2025" "drq version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
drq \- A directory comparison utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B drq
[OPTIONS] DIR1 DIR2
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B drq
compares the contents of two directories and reports missing or differing files. 
It supports filtering by file extensions and provides options for detailed output.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --exclude=ext1,ext2
Exclude files with the specified extensions. Accepts comma-separated values.
.TP
.B --noexclude
Disable default exclusions for common temp files (e.g., *~, .DS_Store).
.TP
.B --include=ext1,ext2
Only compare files with the specified extensions. Accepts comma-separated values.
.TP
.B --details[=N|all]
Show detailed differences. If 'N' is provided, show up to N lines per difference. If 'all' is provided, show full diffs.

.SH EXAMPLES
Compare two directories:
.IP
.B drq ~/bin ~/backup/bin
.PP
Compare directories but exclude `.log` and `.tmp` files:
.IP
.B drq --exclude=log,tmp ~/project1 ~/project2
.PP
Show up to 20 lines of differences:
.IP
.B drq --details=20 ~/dirA ~/dirB

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Anthony Francis and ChatGPT.

.SH SEE ALSO
diff(1), find(1)
